elements.description: The Self-Portrait Project (SPP) is a system and method for self-representation using a two-way mirror, camera, and remote control, and is inspired by, and rooted in, the mantra held by social change movements around the world: “nothing about us without us”. Since 2009, Andy Lin has been empowering people in the telling of their own visual stories on their own terms. Via its unique system, SPP enables eye-to-eye contact between the model/photographer and observer, and through the mirror embodies a visceral, uniquely vulnerable view of its participants. The Self-Portrait Project begins with a metaphorical premise: that to catalyze a positive and healing inertia in the world, one must first see one's self honestly in the mirror and then, to see one’s self reflected in others.
elements.label: The Self-Portrait Project: See Yourself Reflected (in others)

elements.attribute-tags: Knowledge Wisdom & Intelligence|Sensemaking & Rationality|Worldview & Wholeness|Arts Media & Culture|Education & Learning|Sessions
elements.description:
Join geometer, designer and artist Ari Lazer for a brief journey into the power of number in space and time as a lens for understanding, not just the implicit order of our natural world, but the gaping expanse of infinity that lies in each tiny crack.  

Geometry as a framework for understanding nature, reveals an elegant simplicity of simple relationships that underlies the manifest world around us.  

But that’s only half the story.  

The counterpoint to the discrete, beautiful and harmonious relationships we find, are the spaces of unreconciled infinities, to which they are inherently intertwined.  

We’ll use music as our lens, and let the weaving of number in space and time reveal a foundational infinity and mystery that’s at the heart of everything we hear, and maybe more.
elements.label: The Ineffable and The Indivisible: The Power of Tiny Infinites to Guide Our Thinking, Understanding and Creative Practice

elements.description: Isabella is a Disability Inclusion Consultant, model, speaker. She was born with a facial cleft. At 19, she was diagnosed with Vascular Ehlers Danlos Syndrome - a connective tissue disorder that impacts the joints, muscles, and primarily the vascular system. Isabella deeply understands the need for connection as the cornerstone to the human condition, and believes that vulnerability is the catalyst to achieving it. Her mission is to see no person with invisible disabilities to go unnoticed or unsupported. She believe the best way to achieve that is to vehemently advocate to create a culture and industry to support this community. Today, she is creating a line of medical grade compression garments in hopes of finding a more comprehensive and affordable solution in this market place.
elements.label: Redefining Compression Garments

elements.description:
In this immersive experience, embark on a transformative journey through dialogue and transformative inquiry. Join artist, Salem Jorden, as she guides you through the potent process of alchemical transmission. Discover how to dissolve the fear that binds and imprisons you, allowing you to reclaim your sovereignty and reconnect with your inner compass.

In this workshop, Salem delves into the concept of "spectacle hives" – energetic constructs that harbor fear and hinder our critical thinking. By understanding their origins and effects, we gain the power to filter the signal through the noise. This ultimately paves the way towards a life lived with greater clarity and purpose.
elements.label: The Signal and The Noise: Dissolution of Fear into Neutrality

elements.attribute-tags: Arts Media & Culture|Spirituality & Religion|Storytelling & Film|Sensemaking & Rationality|Networks & Connectivity|Sessions
elements.description:
We’ve realized various experiences of division through identity such as race, gender, sexuality, social class or religion, and we’ve experienced negativity by attaching ideas onto humanity, such as “humans are destroying nature” and “humans never stop war”. We wanted to change the world by solving those issues.

But we cannot change by trying to change the world. Rather, the world will naturally be recreated because we let go of old attachments and judgements we put on ourselves. Let’s unseal ourselves from those ideas we have inherited over centuries. What can we see in the new human on the new Earth?

Through magnificent nature, exquisite visions and healing sound, this film project explores the sensations of the state of being the new sacred human.
elements.label: Feel the Sensation As New Human

elements.attribute-tags: Circular Economy|Cooperative Economics|Creation Making Manufacturing|Innovation Invention & Ideation|Regenerative Economy & Systems|Systems Design & Thinking|Sessions
elements.description:
How can we re-imagine our current manufacturing system to incorporate natural systems? How can we take waste products from one system and use them as inputs for another?

 In this presentation TO will explain how he came to his current project "Reishi Bonsai Bowl" in which he co-creates art with his collaborator... The Reishi Mushroom - to create a unique and one-of-a-kind piece of art that has instilled in its process -regeneration, nutrient cycling, systems thinking and much more. 
He will also be sharing his larger vision to build the first Open Source MycoMakerSpace- using this project as both a jump-off point as well as a sandbox to test out various methods and ideas for said MycoMakerSpace.

Come hang!
elements.label: Creating in Collaboration with Nature : Woodworking w/ Mushrooms
